This article is a notice from the White House Office of the Press Secretary regarding the continuation of the national emergency with respect to the Western Balkans. The national emergency was declared on June 26, 2001, to deal with the threat posed by extremist violence and acts obstructing the implementation of peace agreements in the region. The President has determined that the actions of individuals in the Western Balkans continue to pose a threat to the national security and foreign policy of the United States. Therefore, the national emergency will continue for another year. This notice will be published in the Federal Register and transmitted to Congress.